      "content": "Mixing drops with warm saline solution can be a good idea, but make sure to use a sterile saline solution and avoid touching the eye or the dropper to your eye or other surfaces to prevent infection. Also, be cautious not to overdo it, as excessive flushing can cause discomfort or even push the infection further into the eye. Just use it as needed, and if the discharge persists or worsens, you should still see a doctor.",
      "source": "target",
